        <xsd:documentation>
            <xhtml:h2  ism:ownerProducer="USA" ism:classification="U"
                >Implementation Notes</xhtml:h2>
            <xhtml:ul >
                <xhtml:li ism:ownerProducer="USA" ism:classification="U">The ICMS schema defines the
                    elements for routing message objects within ITS. In addition to the message
                    contents and any attachments, it contains other metadata such as the originator,
                    recipient(s), security markings and delivery precedence.</xhtml:li>
                <xhtml:li ism:ownerProducer="USA" ism:classification="U">Refer to the <xhtml:i>
                    <xhtml:a href="../../Documents/ITS-OM/DesItsOmXml.pdf">XML Data Encoding Specification for
                            Information Transport Service Organizational Messaging</xhtml:a>
                    </xhtml:i> (ITS-OM.XML DES) for additional information</xhtml:li>
                <xhtml:li ism:ownerProducer="USA" ism:classification="U"
                    >The IC Messaging Service (ICMS) XML provides the base XML elements used to
                    define an information object allowed to be transported via ITS/OM.  This XML
                    uses the IC standard for Information Security Marking (IC ISM) V5 XML attributes
                    to provide security markings for the information.</xhtml:li>
            </xhtml:ul>
            <xhtml:p ism:ownerProducer="USA" ism:classification="U"> The root element for ITS-OM is: 
                <xhtml:ul>
                    <xhtml:li ism:ownerProducer="USA" ism:classification="U">
                        <xhtml:a href="ITS-OM_xsd_Element_icms_Icms.html">icms:Icms</xhtml:a>
                    </xhtml:li>
                </xhtml:ul>
            </xhtml:p>
            
        </xsd:documentation>
        <xsd:documentation>
            <xhtml:h2  ism:ownerProducer="USA" ism:classification="U"
                >Creators</xhtml:h2>
            <xhtml:p  ism:ownerProducer="USA" ism:classification="U"
                >Office of the Director of National Intelligence Intelligence Community Chief
                Information Officer</xhtml:p>
        </xsd:documentation>
